1
00:00:14,575 --> 00:00:20,013
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,848 --> 00:00:28,755
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,823 --> 00:00:34,193
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,262 --> 00:00:38,323
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:44,470
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,206 --> 00:00:52,112
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,514 --> 00:00:57,006
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,084 --> 00:01:04,047
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,125 --> 00:01:11,190
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,265 --> 00:01:17,932
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,406 --> 00:01:27,906
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:40,272 --> 00:01:42,672
This is not good,
looks like a storm is coming.

13
00:01:43,141 --> 00:01:43,698
What?

14
00:01:46,511 --> 00:01:47,341
Idate...

15
00:01:47,913 --> 00:01:53,909
<i>Run Idate Run!</i>
<i>Nagi Island Awaits!</i>

16
00:02:01,626 --> 00:02:02,991
Aoi... Rokusho!

17
00:02:04,396 --> 00:02:06,330
I thought you had run away.

18
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,867
Wasn't running away
your specialty?

19
00:02:11,903 --> 00:02:12,767
Shut up!

20
00:02:13,505 --> 00:02:14,699
I'm different from you!

21
00:02:15,407 --> 00:02:19,002
No, you are the same kind
of human as I am.

22
00:02:19,945 --> 00:02:22,140
A betrayer who doesn't trust others.

23
00:02:22,814 --> 00:02:26,477
Betraying your own brother,
walking away from the village

24
00:02:27,118 --> 00:02:30,781
and capable of thinking only of yourself.
The worst kind of man.

25
00:02:35,427 --> 00:02:38,021
Such a man...
doesn't deserve to live!

26
00:02:50,909 --> 00:02:51,739
Die!

27
00:02:57,949 --> 00:03:00,179
Sakura, is your wound okay?

28
00:03:00,518 --> 00:03:01,075
Uh huh.

29
00:03:01,786 --> 00:03:03,413
A wound like this is nothing.

30
00:03:04,222 --> 00:03:05,052
But...

31
00:03:06,157 --> 00:03:07,454
Those Rain Ninja... huh?

32
00:03:07,826 --> 00:03:08,383
Yes.

33
00:03:08,593 --> 00:03:11,562
Hah, they're nothing!

34
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:15,361
No, it's not that!
If they're headed towards Idate...

35
00:03:18,236 --> 00:03:20,329
Oh! Idate is in danger!

36
00:03:20,438 --> 00:03:22,531
That's what I've been saying!

37
00:03:25,944 --> 00:03:28,606
Hey, Naruto!
This is no time to be playing around.

38
00:03:29,281 --> 00:03:29,975
No!

39
00:03:30,482 --> 00:03:31,710
They're here now.

40
00:03:38,256 --> 00:03:38,915
<i>Naruto!</i>

41
00:03:39,724 --> 00:03:40,656
<i>Lucky us!</i>

42
00:03:41,293 --> 00:03:43,420
<i>We are invincible in water.</i>

43
00:03:46,798 --> 00:03:48,425
<i>Geez, what a troublesome guy.</i>

44
00:03:49,501 --> 00:03:51,696
They've now fallen into our trap.

45
00:03:52,971 --> 00:03:54,404
<i>Water Clone Jutsu!</i>

46
00:04:04,082 --> 00:04:04,980
<i>Sakura!</i>

47
00:04:13,124 --> 00:04:15,115
<i>Shadow Clone Jutsu!</i>

48
00:04:25,036 --> 00:04:29,530
<i>How stupid. What use can</i>
<i>Shadow Clones have in this situation?</i>

49
00:04:30,008 --> 00:04:34,104
<i>There's no way they can defeat</i>
<i>our Water Clones in water.</i>

50
00:04:34,679 --> 00:04:37,147
<i>Even if you try to trick us,</i>

51
00:04:37,582 --> 00:04:40,881
<i>I'm hanging on to the real body</i>
<i>right here.</i>

52
00:05:06,044 --> 00:05:07,443
<i>What are they trying to do?</i>

53
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,232
<i>N-No way!</i>

54
00:05:31,736 --> 00:05:35,137
<i>What a whirlpool...</i>
<i>Chakra is intertwined in it!</i>

55
00:05:35,573 --> 00:05:37,063
<i>Naruto...you...</i>

56
00:05:43,448 --> 00:05:44,745
<i>This is the application</i>
<i>of the first step</i>

57
00:05:44,816 --> 00:05:47,717
<i>in my training for</i>
<i>the Rasengan!</i>

58
00:05:54,559 --> 00:05:55,355
<i>Sakura!</i>

59
00:05:59,798 --> 00:06:01,789
<i>Sakura, hang in there!</i>

60
00:06:14,212 --> 00:06:16,077
Sakura! Just hang in there!

61
00:06:16,614 --> 00:06:18,047
Come on! Sakura!

62
00:06:34,766 --> 00:06:35,460
Sakura!

63
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,433
Pull yourself together! Sakura!

64
00:06:38,536 --> 00:06:41,903
<i>I-I guess...I've got...to...do it...</i>

65
00:06:46,811 --> 00:06:48,278
<i>S-Sasuke...</i>

66
00:06:49,814 --> 00:06:51,714
<i>I'd like it if Sasuke is the one to do...</i>

67
00:06:52,684 --> 00:06:54,447
<i>the CPR...</i>

68
00:07:00,091 --> 00:07:01,922
<i>S-Sakura...</i>

69
00:07:05,363 --> 00:07:07,160
What the hell are you doing, idiot!

70
00:07:11,336 --> 00:07:11,995
Sasuke?

71
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:15,931
We don't have any time to spare.
We need to meet up with Idate.

72
00:07:17,509 --> 00:07:18,703
Wait, Sasuke.

73
00:07:22,914 --> 00:07:24,848
Hey... Don't leave me.

74
00:07:40,832 --> 00:07:41,799
It's about time...

75
00:07:42,967 --> 00:07:45,731
Fukusuke reaches Modoroki Shrine.

76
00:07:50,141 --> 00:07:53,076
There's no chance for you
to win now.

77
00:07:59,317 --> 00:08:02,775
You can't even run
or stand up now.

78
00:08:06,658 --> 00:08:09,252
When that pain spreads
throughout your whole body,

79
00:08:09,894 --> 00:08:12,328
you'll reach a different finish line.

80
00:08:18,136 --> 00:08:20,366
The finish line of death.

81
00:08:30,949 --> 00:08:35,682
What are you thinking of doing
with that dirty knife?

82
00:08:38,489 --> 00:08:39,478
Don't touch it!

83
00:08:52,904 --> 00:08:56,704
Looks like you still don't understand
your situation.

84
00:08:58,543 --> 00:09:01,535
All you have to do is run away.

85
00:09:02,513 --> 00:09:05,710
You have no right to even
the slightest bit of integrity.

86
00:09:22,634 --> 00:09:23,328
<i>Boss...</i>

87
00:09:28,706 --> 00:09:29,468
I'm sorry...

88
00:09:30,508 --> 00:09:31,167
Boss...

89
00:09:33,544 --> 00:09:35,102
I couldn't keep...

90
00:09:37,815 --> 00:09:39,180
the promise I made with you.

91
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,180
Idate!

92
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:56,864
You bastard!

93
00:10:06,712 --> 00:10:08,509
<i>Darn, what a downpour.</i>

94
00:10:09,314 --> 00:10:11,646
Are you the boss of the Rain Ninja?!

95
00:10:14,119 --> 00:10:16,883
Looks like it was too hard
a task for them.

96
00:10:17,456 --> 00:10:18,980
Even if they were
the same Genin as you,

97
00:10:19,057 --> 00:10:21,287
seems like the Hidden Leaf ones
are better.

98
00:10:23,395 --> 00:10:24,054
This is terrible...

99
00:10:26,365 --> 00:10:30,096
But can Genin level Ninja
fight against me?

100
00:10:31,069 --> 00:10:32,297
Shut up!

101
00:10:36,942 --> 00:10:37,465
Above!

102
00:10:52,290 --> 00:10:54,383
Humph... So that's your level, after all.

103
00:10:55,193 --> 00:10:58,094
I'll use the same method
I used on Idate,

104
00:10:59,664 --> 00:11:01,564
and send you to hell.

105
00:11:04,302 --> 00:11:06,634
No need to waste my Chakra.

106
00:11:09,441 --> 00:11:10,135
Sakura!

107
00:11:15,313 --> 00:11:16,712
Th-These darned things...

108
00:11:17,482 --> 00:11:19,780
Those are poisoned needles specially
made by the Hidden Rain Village.

109
00:11:20,385 --> 00:11:22,285
They will send you to hell
in a few minutes,

110
00:11:22,387 --> 00:11:24,184
no matter how strong you are.

111
00:11:24,322 --> 00:11:26,290
Don't you look down on us! Bastard...!

112
00:11:31,663 --> 00:11:33,858
Looks like Fukusuke has reached
Modoroki Shrine.

113
00:11:34,666 --> 00:11:36,463
Die gasping

114
00:11:36,735 --> 00:11:39,431
It's a death
that fits you Genin brats well.

115
00:11:48,213 --> 00:11:50,340
Is Wagarashi winning this one too?

116
00:11:50,615 --> 00:11:52,947
Isn't there a God or Buddha
in this world?

117
00:11:53,919 --> 00:11:57,047
I miss the old times when
Jirocho was in charge.

118
00:12:03,562 --> 00:12:06,395
Terrible, terrible, I'm drenched.

119
00:12:06,565 --> 00:12:08,226
You are amazing, Fukusuke.

120
00:12:08,366 --> 00:12:12,063
Keep on running to the goal,
and make our Boss Wagarashi happy.

121
00:12:13,138 --> 00:12:14,628
Watch it, you scum.

122
00:12:15,107 --> 00:12:16,870
Who do you think you are talking to?

123
00:12:17,342 --> 00:12:18,070
What?

124
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:22,540
My victory is already assured.
Let me relax for a while.

125
00:12:22,614 --> 00:12:24,309
Bastard, think you're so hot?!

126
00:12:24,382 --> 00:12:25,007
Cut it out...

127
00:12:25,117 --> 00:12:25,674
Brother...

128
00:12:26,218 --> 00:12:28,083
What if something goes wrong
during the race?

129
00:12:28,386 --> 00:12:30,513
Who knows what our boss
will do to us.

130
00:12:31,256 --> 00:12:32,223
All right.

131
00:12:32,924 --> 00:12:33,982
<i>Just wait and see.</i>

132
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,767
Darn, that bastard!

133
00:12:44,035 --> 00:12:45,559
Naruto, Sasuke...

134
00:12:46,438 --> 00:12:47,097
Take this.

135
00:12:48,006 --> 00:12:49,405
Sakura... What's that?

136
00:12:52,444 --> 00:12:53,934
Before leaving the Leaf Village

137
00:12:55,547 --> 00:12:57,242
Lady Tsunade handed this to me.

138
00:12:57,916 --> 00:13:01,044
<i>Take this with you.</i>
<i>I am sure it will come in handy.</i>

139
00:13:01,586 --> 00:13:02,985
Old Lady Tsunade?

140
00:13:07,759 --> 00:13:09,750
I think he'll recover
consciousness now.

141
00:13:11,196 --> 00:13:13,061
Sasuke and Naruto,
you take this, too.

142
00:13:13,398 --> 00:13:14,592
O-Okay.

143
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:19,661
Also, we'll be too cold here,
so we need to move somewhere else.

144
00:13:24,075 --> 00:13:24,973
Brother!

145
00:13:32,517 --> 00:13:35,509
Look! I've finally become
a Ninja, too!

146
00:13:36,521 --> 00:13:37,146
I see...

147
00:13:37,289 --> 00:13:39,951
I've got to become the best
in everything!

148
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:44,186
I'll train hard,
and complete lots of missions.

149
00:13:44,663 --> 00:13:46,722
And I'll become a Chunin super fast.

150
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,031
Then after that, a Jonin.

151
00:13:49,501 --> 00:13:51,594
I'm going to be like you, Brother!

152
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:55,000
I'm Idate, the Swift Runner
making headway in life.

153
00:13:56,074 --> 00:13:56,631
Brother?

154
00:14:00,445 --> 00:14:02,140
Listen Idate...

155
00:14:03,582 --> 00:14:05,049
In the world of Shinobi,

156
00:14:05,383 --> 00:14:08,648
there is something more important
than success or power.

157
00:14:08,987 --> 00:14:10,113
Something more important?

158
00:14:11,056 --> 00:14:15,288
Until you understand that,
it's too early for you to talk that way.

159
00:14:24,936 --> 00:14:25,527
Oh!

160
00:14:25,737 --> 00:14:27,261
He's conscious now.

161
00:14:28,506 --> 00:14:29,404
Are you okay?

162
00:14:29,908 --> 00:14:31,876
What happened to Aoi?!

163
00:14:32,911 --> 00:14:33,843
He disappeared...

164
00:14:34,212 --> 00:14:36,578
So that Rain Ninja is called Aoi?

165
00:14:39,084 --> 00:14:41,882
Idate, do you know him?

166
00:14:43,655 --> 00:14:44,383
He...

167
00:14:45,423 --> 00:14:47,618
was a teacher when
I was in the Leaf Village.

168
00:14:47,926 --> 00:14:50,087
You... are from the Leaf Village?

169
00:14:50,795 --> 00:14:53,764
Aoi... betrayed the Leaf Village

170
00:14:54,266 --> 00:14:55,790
and became a Jonin of the Hidden Rain.

171
00:14:56,501 --> 00:14:58,765
What the hell do you mean?

172
00:15:01,539 --> 00:15:02,665
Not yet.

173
00:15:03,308 --> 00:15:04,639
You have to rest a little more.

174
00:15:06,278 --> 00:15:07,336
How is your hand there?

175
00:15:09,514 --> 00:15:10,310
That hand...

176
00:15:10,582 --> 00:15:12,311
You kept it clenched all this time.

177
00:15:18,156 --> 00:15:21,216
Darn! I'd come all this way,
and yet I!

178
00:15:21,293 --> 00:15:23,318
It's too early to give up!

179
00:15:23,662 --> 00:15:26,358
And you tell us that you were once
a Shinobi of the Leaf?!

180
00:15:27,899 --> 00:15:30,868
I forgot all about the Leaf...

181
00:15:31,403 --> 00:15:32,995
the moment
I walked away from the village.

182
00:15:33,972 --> 00:15:35,269
You walked away from the village?

183
00:15:37,809 --> 00:15:43,543
I was depressed after failing
the first test of the Chunin Exam.

184
00:15:45,517 --> 00:15:47,508
That was close, Idate...

185
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,087
Don't take it so hard.

186
00:15:53,825 --> 00:15:57,522
There are ways to become
a Chunin other than the Chunin Exam.

187
00:15:58,430 --> 00:15:59,294
Really?!

188
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:03,099
Yes, really.

189
00:16:04,235 --> 00:16:05,896
Just do as I tell you.

190
00:16:06,838 --> 00:16:07,566
Okay!

191
00:16:15,447 --> 00:16:16,414
Aoi Sensei...

192
00:16:17,615 --> 00:16:18,445
Idate...

193
00:16:19,417 --> 00:16:22,784
Aoi Sensei,
I'd brought them as you told me to.

194
00:16:25,623 --> 00:16:26,248
All right.

195
00:16:27,058 --> 00:16:30,824
These are indeed the Scroll of Sealing
and the legendary blade,

196
00:16:30,895 --> 00:16:34,296
the Blade of the Thunder God, believed to
have been used by the Second Hokage.

197
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,428
Well done, Idate.

198
00:16:37,202 --> 00:16:39,727
Now I can become a Chunin, right?

199
00:16:40,572 --> 00:16:42,267
Sure you can...

200
00:16:44,642 --> 00:16:46,405
in the Village Hidden in the Rain.

201
00:16:50,148 --> 00:16:52,708
You are leaving
the Leaf together with me,

202
00:16:53,318 --> 00:16:54,910
taking these as gifts to them.

203
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:56,114
But...

204
00:16:59,524 --> 00:17:00,752
Of course.

205
00:17:01,059 --> 00:17:04,722
There's no way you can get away with
stealing the village's treasures.

206
00:17:04,829 --> 00:17:06,057
You tricked me!

207
00:17:06,798 --> 00:17:11,201
To survive in this world,
you must not believe in others...

208
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,237
Remember that.

209
00:17:15,673 --> 00:17:18,141
Well, what are you going to do, Idate?

210
00:17:19,110 --> 00:17:22,102
Either way, you are already
a Rogue Ninja.

211
00:17:24,549 --> 00:17:27,814
You'll be chained in jail for life,
if you are lucky.

212
00:17:32,524 --> 00:17:37,860
<i>You'll be chained in jail for life,</i>
<i>if you are lucky.</i>

213
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:48,237
Ever since then,
I haven't returned to the village.

214
00:17:49,641 --> 00:17:53,133
I am an irresponsible man
who can't do a single thing right.

215
00:17:53,878 --> 00:17:55,812
But Boss Jirocho believed in me.

216
00:17:57,182 --> 00:18:01,812
Even though I'd never
been of any use to him.

217
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:04,012
Boss Jirocho had faith in me!

218
00:18:04,856 --> 00:18:06,824
And yet, I...!

219
00:18:13,198 --> 00:18:13,823
<i>He's...</i>

220
00:18:15,667 --> 00:18:18,227
<i>He's...like the old me...</i>

221
00:18:20,705 --> 00:18:24,903
<i>No one will ever accept you!</i>
<i>Die Naruto!</i>

222
00:18:27,278 --> 00:18:28,609
<i>Duck down, Naruto!</i>

223
00:18:34,252 --> 00:18:36,982
I'm... a worthless guy...

224
00:18:37,922 --> 00:18:40,117
<i>W-Why?</i>

225
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:43,487
<i>Because we are the same.</i>

226
00:18:44,262 --> 00:18:46,230
<i>He's like me of the old days.</i>

227
00:18:47,098 --> 00:18:48,565
I go around and around,
and get nowhere...

228
00:18:49,968 --> 00:18:51,560
I can't do anything right.

229
00:18:52,337 --> 00:18:53,634
Aoi is right.

230
00:18:53,705 --> 00:18:56,606
I have... no right to live

231
00:18:56,674 --> 00:18:57,902
You idiot!

232
00:18:58,643 --> 00:19:02,409
There's a person
who still trusts you, right?

233
00:19:03,214 --> 00:19:05,444
<i>I know, Naruto.</i>

234
00:19:06,251 --> 00:19:11,314
<i>You felt alone...</i>
<i>and you were suffering!</i>

235
00:19:11,589 --> 00:19:14,183
One is enough!

236
00:19:18,162 --> 00:19:19,925
The race isn't over yet!

237
00:19:20,498 --> 00:19:24,127
You never know how things will turn out
unless you try until the very end.

238
00:19:26,137 --> 00:19:26,728
But...

239
00:19:28,072 --> 00:19:29,232
Stand up now!

240
00:19:29,307 --> 00:19:31,901
Naruto, it's not possible!
Idate's body is still...

241
00:19:31,976 --> 00:19:35,571
If he can't run,
then I'll carry him on my back and run!

242
00:19:37,348 --> 00:19:39,407
The opponent must already be
in Modoroki Shrine...

243
00:19:40,251 --> 00:19:41,775
Don't give up!

244
00:19:41,953 --> 00:19:43,011
Hey... Naruto...

245
00:19:43,922 --> 00:19:44,854
Sasuke...

246
00:19:46,324 --> 00:19:48,053
Let's leave it to Naruto here.

247
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:51,422
Jirocho is waiting for you, right?

248
00:19:51,996 --> 00:19:53,327
Pull yourself together!

249
00:20:11,983 --> 00:20:14,679
Boss, don't you think
he actually ran away?

250
00:20:16,688 --> 00:20:17,347
He'll come.

251
00:20:18,556 --> 00:20:20,387
I believe in Idate!

252
